HEADWORD: Spectroheliograph
<hw>Spec`tro*he"li*o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Astrophysics)</fld> <def>An apparatus for making
spectroheliograms, consisting of a spectroscopic camera used in
combination with a telescope, and provided with clockwork for moving the
sun's image across the slit.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Spec`tro*he`li*o*graph"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spectrological</ent>⟦br⟧
